ron system','1','1236536858ATTG'),('You can now edit the preferences of this task','1','1236656718FWVX'),('Description of your task to help you organize it<br>','1','1236791960OSDP'),('Type of your task<br><br>','1','1236791960OSDQ'),('Frequency of your task.<br>This parameter is only used if you selected the periodic type <span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">\"frequency</span>\"<br>','1','1237202239LEER'),('<span style=\"font-weight: bold; font-style: italic;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Frequency</span> :</span> The system will launch the task every X minutes.<br><br><span style=\"font-style: italic; font-weight: bold;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Cron Frequency</span> :</span> The system will launch the task every X minutes depending on the field \"<span style=\"font-style: italic;\">Cron</span>\".<br><span style=\"font-weight: bold; font-style: italic;\"><br><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Date</span> :</span><span style=\"font-style: italic;\"> </span>The system will launch the task only one time at the specified \"<span style=\"font-style: italic;\">next date</span>\".<span style=\"font-weight: bold; font-style: italic;\"></span><br>','1','1237202239LEES'),('If you selected the periodic type \"Cron Frequency\", the next send date will be calculated based on this parameter.<br>','1','1237202239LEET'),('Fixed date','1','1237395235EOTF'),('Specify the overall maximum number of processes the scheduler can handle.<br>','1','1240906945NFCJ'),('Enter the time limit ( in seconds ) for the scheduler.<br>The process won\'t launch any task after this time limit.<br>Depending on your configuration, the process may stop before this time limit and adopt the value of the maximum execution time from your server.','1','1240906945NFCK'),('Defines if the visitor will automatically launch the scheduler system.<br><br>If you configured a Cron Task, please turn Off this option.','1','1240906945NFCL'),('Done','1','1242282449PIPC'),('This view enables you to specify <span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">periodic tasks</span>.<br><ul><li>You can specify a basic frequency if you select the Periodic type \"<span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Frequency</span>\".</li><li>If you need more advanced frequency, you can select the Periodic type \"<span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Cron Frequency</span>\" and enter <a target=\"_blank\" title=\"\" href=\"http://www.joobi.co/index.php?option=com_jlinks&controller=redirect&link=cron_jscheduler\">a cron frequency</a> in the field \"<span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Cron</span>\".<br></li><li>If you select the Periodic type<span style=\"font-weight: bold;\"> </span>\"<span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Date</span>\", your task will only be executed one time at the selected <span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">next date</span>.</li></ul>Some of tasks require more parameters to work properly.<br>You will be able to modify those parameters <span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">after saving your task</span>.<br>','1','1290669833IHWS'),('Launched Tasks : $nbResults','1','1298294163YKW'),('No Task was Launched...','1','1298294164ESOK'),('Processes','1','1298294166ECLV'),('Max Time','1','1298294168JDHE'),('Max Process','1','1298294168JDHF'),('Enter here the allowable number of processes run on parallel for this task.<br><br>','1','1298294168JDHG'),('Enter here the priority of this task.<br>0 is the highest priority, 254 is the lowest priority','1','1298294168JDHH'),('Specify the maximum frequency the scheduler can run ( in seconds ).<br>This parameter is a simple security to don\'t launch too often the scheduler so a delay of minimum X seconds will separate the last run date and the next run date.<br>','1','1298294169DGIV');
INSERT IGNORE INTO `#__translation_en` (`text`,`auto`,`imac`) VALUES ('Advance','1','1298294169DGIW'),('Max Tasks','1','1298294169DGIX'),('Specify the maximum number of tasks the scheduler can process.<br>','1','1298294169DGIY'),('Max Processes','1','1298294169DGIZ'),('Since','1','1298294170PECN'),('Column1','1','1298294170PECO'),('Nextdate','1','1298294170PECP'),('Lastdate','1','1298294170PECQ'),('Column2','1','1298294170PECR'),('Ptype','1','1298294170PECS'),('Maxtime','1','1298294170PECT'),('Maxprocess','1','1298294170PECU'),('Scheduler can not proceed','1','1298350272MURB'),('Scheduler Processes','1','1298350272MURC'),('In','1','1298350272MURD'),('The task that is currently running either in parallel or not','1','1298350273IXBE'),('The date the process has been created','1','1298350273IXBF'),('Memory Limit','1','1298350274FGVE'),('Specify the maximum limit in MB you want the memory can handle.<br>','1','1298350274FGVF'),('Server Background Tasks','1','1298350274FGVG'),('Server Tasks Preferences','1','1298350274FGVH'),('<ul><li>Only those running processes are showed in this view.</li><li>Every killed or finished process is automatically removed. </li></ul>','1','1298350275LTMN'),('Launch a Parallel Process','1','1298350275LTMO'),('Cron System','1','1298350446IEXG'),('Scheduled Tasks','1','1298888291HSWK'),('Scheduler launched!','1','1299163902NDIX'),('Specify a password in launching the task as protection to the site.<br>','1','1299642742KTUN'),('Use Password','1','1299642847MBBJ'),('An error occured in the processing...','1','1300773865DUMM'),('Every','1','1301380691ICEI'),('','1','1304525968YBL'),('Attempt','1','1311850163FKKV'),('Next Cron','1','1315887118PXIR'),('Show the next valid cron task.<br>','1','1315887122AMOM'),('Ready now, since','1','1369751059DSKE'),('Last Triggered','1','1373207636DEVC'),('Cron URL','1','1373207636DEVD'),('Show the date when the cron task was last triggered.<br>','1','1373207637APRV'),('This is the URL you should trigger from your server or from another website.<br>','1','1373207637APRW'),('Verify that the Cron task plugin is published.','1','1374795728LREB'),('Verify your cron external cron trask because it has nto triggered the site.','1','1374795728LREC'),('The Tasks are background task that applications need to work properly.  The server execute those task in the background. This view enables you to monitor those tasks and modify or unpublish them.<br><br><ul><li>If you select a task and then click on \'<span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Process</span>\', you will force the scheduler to execute the selected task, even it\'s not time to do it or if the task is not published.</li><li>A <span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Core</span> task is a task required by one of the applications. A core task can not be deleted but you can be unpublished.</li></ul><ul><li>The <span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Processes</span> column tells you the number of processes currently running and the maximum number of processes set (Currently Running Processes /  Maximum Process). <br></li></ul><div style=\"margin-left: 80px;\">If the value is <span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">green</span>, everything is good.<br>If the value is <span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">orange</span>, maximum number of processes is reached.<br>If the value is <span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">red</span>, the number of currently running process exceeds the maximum number of processes set. You might simply delete the running task. It will reset the scheduler.<br></div><br>Only user with at least <span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Administrator</span> access level can create, modify or delete a Task.<br><br><div style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">This is the URL to use to trigger the cron task:<br>{widget:site}index.php?option=com_jcenter&controller=scheduler&task=process&tmpl=component&password=</span><br><span style=\"font-style: italic;\"></span></div><div style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-style: italic;\">(enter the password if you have set one. Copy/paste this url on your browser to see if the scheduler application get launched properly)</span><br></div><br>','1','1380064772GVOO'),('<span style=\"font-weight: bold;\"></span>The tasks can be executed with a specific frequency ( for example every Day ) or at a specific date in the future.<br><br><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">How does it work?</span><br>To launch those tasks, the scheduler needs to be triggered by something...<br><ul><li>Any visit on your website can trigger the system (so no visit means no task run!)<br>In that case you have to turn ON the option \"User Cron System\".<br><br></li><li><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">OR</span> an <a target=\"_NEW\" title=\"\" href=\"http://www.joobi.co/index.php?option=com_jlinks&controller=redirect&link=trigger_jscheduler\">external system can trigger the scheduler</a> application by accessing the url :<br><br><br><div style=\"text-align: center;\">     <span style=\"font-weight: bold;\"></span><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">{widget:site}index.php?option=com_jcenter&controller=scheduler&task=process&tmpl=component</span><span style=\"font-style: italic;\"></span><br><span style=\"font-style: italic;\"></span></div><div style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-style: italic;\">(you can copy/paste this url on your browser to see if the scheduler application get launched properly)</span><br></div><br>    <span style=\"font-weight: bold;\"></span><br>This second solution is recommended as the system will be launched at fixed dates and won\'t depend on your website traffic.<br>In that case you can turn OFF the option \"User Cron System\".<br></li></ul><br>','1','1380064772GVOP'),('Scheduler Report from {widget:sitename} at {widget:time|format=2}','1','1380064772GVOQ'),('It appears that your server time setting is not correct!','1','1382065652HZGO'),('Your time','1','1382065664QQKX'),('Verified Server time','1','1382065664QQKY'),('The time based on your timezone.<br>','1','1382065665JEHW'),('Parallel Tasks','1','1397755348IVCW'),('Define if the task triggered by the cron task should be run in parallel by creating new processes or in one single go.<div>Parallel is better but some server create issue when launching new urls in parallel.<br><div><br><br></div></div>','1','1397755349MIED'),('Identifier','1','1398436917DTKC'),('The cron task has not been run for more than four hours, please check your setting in the General Preferences.','1','1405633010MFWR'),('The cron task is important for the good functioning of the website.','1','1405633010MFWS'),('Yes to force the use of a password into the Cron Task URL (only if external or Joobi).<br><span style=\"color: rgb(204, 0, 0); text-decoration: underline;\">Note:</span> even though you dont use password in the Cron Task URL, it is still required because it is used internally to secure the cron task.<br><br>','1','1418159494SYHX'),('The Scheduler system at {widget:site} has been triggered at {widget:time|format=2}.<br><br>{widget:param|name=report}<br><br><br><br><div style=\"text-align: center;\"><a target=\"\" title=\"Joobi\" href=\"http://www.joobi.co\">Powered by Joobi</a><br></div>','1','1418159495CHIF'),('Reference UTC time','1','1436410864OYRA'),('This is the UTC reference time, correspond also to the GMT time zone.','1','1436410865NXKH');
