e link in the <span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Grades</span> column.</li></ul><span style=\"text-decoration: underline; font-style: italic; font-weight: bold;\">About License:</span><br><ul><li>If you have a token you can simply click on <span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Enter token</span> and follow instruction.</li><li>You can use the button <span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Refresh</span> to refresh all your licenses. It will re-actualize all your licenses.<br></li></ul>','1','1418159313RUIV'),('This is a list of all possible translation in any installed language:<br><br>1. To find your translation first select the proper language in the pick-list.<br>2. Choose your application<br>3. Click on the \"Edit\" button to edit the translation.<br>4. In case you do not find the proper string look for it in the main library in jCenter or jApps.<br><br>','1','1418159313RUIW'),('<span style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\">Example of strings:</span><br><br>TR1242010181DZGB=Successfully Ordered $NUMBER $ELEMENT<br><br><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 51, 255);\">IMPORTANT</span>: <br>Make sure to respect the punctuation, cases and spacing as much as possible.<br>Sometimes you might see HTML tags or { tag: ... } in the definition, please leave it the way it is.<br><br><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 51, 255);\">VERY IMPORTANT: </span><br>Please do not touch the first string before the equal sign ( TR1242010181DZGB= ), it will result in translation not working. <br>The text to be translated is everything after the equal sign.<br><br><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 51, 255);\">VARIABLES</span>:<br>When you see a UPPER CASE string with a dollars sign in front ( $ELEMENT ), DO NOT translate, as it will be replaced by a variable or other string. However if you language require to reorder the works and the variable feel free to do so. The UPPER name of the of the variable give you an indication of what it will be replaced with.<br><br><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 51, 255);\">FINAL WORD</span><br>if you are looking for a string and dont find it, it might be in the main library so look for it into jCenter or jApps translation.<br><br>','1','1418159313RUIX'),('<p style=\"line-height: 1.4em;\">Please note that the site where you enter the API key FIRST will be the only site you are entitled for free support. <br>If you have a production site and a development site you need to decide if you prefer getting support for the production site or for the development site.<br>It is not possible to change the site on which you get primary support at a later time.<br> Should you have further question please <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://www.joobi.co/r.php?l=support\">contact the support.</a><br></p>','1','1418159317GYIO'),('Impossible to publish Widget without the application \"$APLLICATION\" installed on the site.','1','1418159318SHOQ'),('Choose','1','1421617710FQCB'),('Uninstall App','1','1421617712NRTN'),('Uninstall Only One App','1','1421617713IRWT'),('Uninstall All Apps','1','1421617713IRWU'),('Remove All Apps and All Data in Database','1','1421617713IRWV'),('Show hidden views','1','1422973803PSLT'),('Show the line number into the log.<div>This require a lot more memory. Use only in debug mode and make sure you have sufficient memory.</div>','1','1422973804PMJX'),('Fields for All Models','1','1423597825SYTZ'),('Allow the same field to be added on all <b>related models</b>.<br><b>Related models</b> are model which share the same table.&nbsp; When looking at the list of models you will see the table name.<br><u>E.g.</u>: the same field could be added to users and contacts model since they share the same table. It can\'t be added to vendors since it is another table.','1','1423597826QYJU'),('Default Page Id','1','1425339791AULI'),('No query has been defined!','1','1425662174IZVW'),('Social Media','1','1425956837EQIA'),('The author of the application','1','1426511377ENBT'),('Not available at the moment. Please check back later.','1','14267263